<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-523-527  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 523 527.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Oct 18 1990 n1236 p26(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What you need is a flexible friend. (Payroll Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goodwin, Candice.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Government restraints through legislation is having an adverseimpact on payroll systems vendors in the UK.andP;  Keeping up withcurrent legislation is exhausting the development resources ofmost payroll systems vendors.andP;  Industry sources note that as soonas a strategy is developed for their customers, the governmentthen steps in with a new legislation which hinders or delays theircorporate plans.andP;  One of the worst case scenarios of statutesimpacting payroll systems is the introduction of a new payrollrelated legislation which includes changes to file structure andsoftware.andP;  Vendors of payroll packages, remember all too well whenemployers were to return and record new information about theirstaff's statutory maternity pay and statutory sick pay.andP;  One ofthe troubling factors that vendors encounter is the timing betweenwhen a legislation is being announced and when it comes intoforce.andP;  The statutory maternity leave pay had a six monthsinterval before it was enforced.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     PayrollManagement ApplicationsGovernment RegulationLegislationSoftware PackagesIndustry Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>